# ğŸ” 9ï¸âƒ£ Best Practices in Production

âœ… Always test updates in staging first
âœ… Avoid unnecessary repositories
âœ… Keep system updated regularly
âœ… Monitor CVEs for installed packages
âœ… Use version locking when required
âœ… Avoid manual compilation unless necessary

---

# ğŸ“Š 10ï¸âƒ£ YUM vs RPM

| Feature               | YUM         | RPM        |
| --------------------- | ----------- | ---------- |
| Dependency resolution | âœ… Automatic | âŒ Manual   |
| High-level management | âœ… Yes       | âŒ No       |
| Install local package | âœ… Yes       | âœ… Yes      |
| Query & verification  | âŒ Limited   | âœ… Advanced |

**Rule of thumb:**
Use `yum/dnf` for installation and updates.
Use `rpm` for inspection and verification.

---

# ğŸ“Œ Key Takeaways

* Package management controls your software lifecycle
* `yum` handles dependencies automatically
* `rpm` provides detailed package inspection
* Repository management is critical for security
* Regular updates protect against vulnerabilities

